# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HollowWorld | Scene: TheHollowWorldWarrior3
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah sat out on the front of the wagon."
    new "Sarah sat out on the front of the wagon."

    old "Slowly the horses pulled it forward, and slowly it buckled from side to side."
    new "Slowly the horses pulled it forward, and slowly it buckled from side to side."

    old "More than a few times over these last few days, Sarah had found herself almost rocked to sleep by the motion of it."
    new "More than a few times over these last few days, Sarah had found herself almost rocked to sleep by the motion of it."

    old "Even now, she felt her eyes go drowsy."
    new "Even now, she felt her eyes go drowsy."

    old "She slapped herself across the face, forcing herself to stay awake."
    new "She slapped herself across the face, forcing herself to stay awake."

    old "This was how the desert preyed on people."
    new "This was how the desert preyed on people."

    old "Seduce you into a moment of laxiety, a single moment where you let your mind slip and forget where you are, and then you'll fall asleep under a scorching sun."
    new "Seduce you into a moment of laxiety, a single moment where you let your mind slip and forget where you are, and then you'll fall asleep under a scorching sun."

    old "Sarah had seen the burned faces of a few soldiers who had just made such a mistake."
    new "Sarah had seen the burned faces of a few soldiers who had just made such a mistake."

    old "The desert was a stranger to the soldiers of the mercenary company, most having been born in Lethram or Mythra."
    new "The desert was a stranger to the soldiers of the mercenary company, most having been born in Lethram or Mythra."

    old "And they were strangers to the desert, who had as uninvited guests intruded upon its home."
    new "And they were strangers to the desert, who had as uninvited guests intruded upon its home."

    old "They didn't want to be here, and the desert didn't want them."
    new "They didn't want to be here, and the desert didn't want them."

    old "And yet, each was condemned to the other, all on the word of a single man."
    new "And yet, each was condemned to the other, all on the word of a single man."

    old "Bagrad was now a good five days behind them, and now even the ruins of civilization had grown rare."
    new "Bagrad was now a good five days behind them, and now even the ruins of civilization had grown rare."

    old "Save for the occasional broken remnant of a statue, the sand dominated everything."
    new "Save for the occasional broken remnant of a statue, the sand dominated everything."

    old "Sarah had imagined the day would play out little different from the other days, until a soldier suddenly came running up."
    new "Sarah had imagined the day would play out little different from the other days, until a soldier suddenly came running up."

    old "Sarah leaned to the edge of the wagon."
    new "Sarah leaned to the edge of the wagon."

    old "General Vaelen requests your immediate presence at the front of the convoy."
    new "General Vaelen requests your immediate presence at the front of the convoy."

    old "Did he say what it was about?"
    new "Did he say what it was about?"

    old "The soldier shook his head."
    new "The soldier shook his head."

    old "No, commander, I was only instructed to inform you."
    new "No, commander, I was only instructed to inform you."

    old "I understand. I'll be there in a moment."
    new "I understand. I'll be there in a moment."

    old "After leaving her cart in the care of Kate, Sarah reported to the front of the convoy."
    new "After leaving her cart in the care of Kate, Sarah reported to the front of the convoy."

    old "As she arrived, she saw Vaelen already standing out ahead of all the other wagons, staring towards the distance."
    new "As she arrived, she saw Vaelen already standing out ahead of all the other wagons, staring towards the distance."

    old "What is going on?"
    new "What is going on?"

    old "Vaelen didn't turn to face her, continuing to stare into the distance."
    new "Vaelen didn't turn to face her, continuing to stare into the distance."

    old "Good, you're here."
    new "Good, you're here."

    old "We have a problem."
    new "We have a problem."

    old "As Sarah walked up closer, she understood it immediately."
    new "As Sarah walked up closer, she understood it immediately."

    old "Vaelen gestured out ahead. He didn't need to say much more."
    new "Vaelen gestured out ahead. He didn't need to say much more."

    old "The road..."
    new "The road..."

    old "Ever since they had left Bagrad, the road they took had become increasingly poor."
    new "Ever since they had left Bagrad, the road they took had become increasingly poor."

    old "But where once it had appeared merely dilapidated, it now crumbled apart all together."
    new "But where once it had appeared merely dilapidated, it now crumbled apart all together."

    old "Nothing remained beyond this point, but desert. Always the desert."
    new "Nothing remained beyond this point, but desert. Always the desert."

    old "Their convoy had reached its limit."
    new "Their convoy had reached its limit."

    old "Sarah could not deny that a part of her was glad knowing that this foolishness had come to an end."
    new "Sarah could not deny that a part of her was glad knowing that this foolishness had come to an end."

    old "I'll order the men to begin preparations."
    new "I'll order the men to begin preparations."

    old "Our supplies will last us the way back and we can hope there remains anything to re-stock in Bagrad."
    new "Our supplies will last us the way back and we can hope there remains anything to re-stock in Bagrad."

    old "Otherwise, we'll have to ration beyond that point, I think the nearest city we can expect to restock is-"
    new "Otherwise, we'll have to ration beyond that point, I think the nearest city we can expect to restock is-"

    old "His voice thundered and carried across the air."
    new "His voice thundered and carried across the air."

    old "We do not turn around."
    new "We do not turn around."

    old "Sarah was stunned, and only felt her shock fade into anger."
    new "Sarah was stunned, and only felt her shock fade into anger."

    old "Are you mad?"
    new "Are you mad?"

    old "She gestured towards the desert."
    new "She gestured towards the desert."

    old "There is no road."
    new "There is no road."

    old "The wagons will sink into the sand, the men won't be able to walk even a quarter of a regular day's march."
    new "The wagons will sink into the sand, the men won't be able to walk even a quarter of a regular day's march."

    old "Vaelen turned to face her."
    new "Vaelen turned to face her."

    old "I didn't ask you to come here and tell me how this is impossible. I need you to tell me how it is possible."
    new "I didn't ask you to come here and tell me how this is impossible. I need you to tell me how it is possible."

    old "Sarah searched his face for any sign of reason, but it was merely blank."
    new "Sarah searched his face for any sign of reason, but it was merely blank."

    old "Behind her, Sarah heard the nearing of footsteps."
    new "Behind her, Sarah heard the nearing of footsteps."

    old "As Sarah turned around, she saw a man walk up towards them."
    new "As Sarah turned around, she saw a man walk up towards them."

    old "Gideon."
    new "Gideon."

    old "Having trouble, are we?"
    new "Having trouble, are we?"

    old "Gideon was one of the other commanders in the mercenary company."
    new "Gideon was one of the other commanders in the mercenary company."

    old "He had a casual air about him, smiling, as though they might as well have been out on a market rather than in the middle of a desert."
    new "He had a casual air about him, smiling, as though they might as well have been out on a market rather than in the middle of a desert."

    old "Yes, in fact, we are."
    new "Yes, in fact, we are."

    old "Sarah stepped towards him."
    new "Sarah stepped towards him."

    old "You need to speak sense to him, he won't listen to me."
    new "You need to speak sense to him, he won't listen to me."

    old "Gideon looked past her towards Vaelen."
    new "Gideon looked past her towards Vaelen."

    old "Well, Vaelen, you know my usual advice is to just listen to Sarah."
    new "Well, Vaelen, you know my usual advice is to just listen to Sarah."

    old "She can be a pain, but at least she'll give you the truth."
    new "She can be a pain, but at least she'll give you the truth."

    old "Vaelen glared at the both of them."
    new "Vaelen glared at the both of them."

    old "I didn't invite her to tell me the truth, nor did I invite you here to gang up with her."
    new "I didn't invite her to tell me the truth, nor did I invite you here to gang up with her."

    old "Sarah is in charge of the vanguard unit and you manage the core."
    new "Sarah is in charge of the vanguard unit and you manage the core."

    old "Together, you oversee more than half of the entire army."
    new "Together, you oversee more than half of the entire army."

    old "I invited you here because together you know better than anyone what our capabilities are, and what our options are."
    new "I invited you here because together you know better than anyone what our capabilities are, and what our options are."

    old "Gideon looked back at Sarah."
    new "Gideon looked back at Sarah."

    old "Options?"
    new "Options?"

    old "He wants to keep marching further into the desert."
    new "He wants to keep marching further into the desert."

    old "But the road stops here."
    new "But the road stops here."

    old "But he won't listen to reason. Maybe he's been out in the sun for too long."
    new "But he won't listen to reason. Maybe he's been out in the sun for too long."

    old "She could see Vaelen didn't appreciate the insult."
    new "She could see Vaelen didn't appreciate the insult."

    old "Go ahead, say whatever you want, but let me make this clear."
    new "Go ahead, say whatever you want, but let me make this clear."

    old "We are going to march on towards our destination, and the two of you will figure out the best way for the army to continue."
    new "We are going to march on towards our destination, and the two of you will figure out the best way for the army to continue."

    old "Should you fail to find me an answer, I'll whip them into the desert naked if I have to."
    new "Should you fail to find me an answer, I'll whip them into the desert naked if I have to."

    old "Vaelen stormed past them."
    new "Vaelen stormed past them."

    old "Bring me a report when you're done, and don't make it more than an hour."
    new "Bring me a report when you're done, and don't make it more than an hour."

    old "With that, Vaelen walked away, back to the lead wagon at the head of the convoy."
    new "With that, Vaelen walked away, back to the lead wagon at the head of the convoy."

    old "Sarah turned to Gideon."
    new "Sarah turned to Gideon."

    old "Gideon...you know Vaelen, you know how he gets...but something is wrong with him."
    new "Gideon...you know Vaelen, you know how he gets...but something is wrong with him."

    old "Gideon looked out towards the end of the road and out across the dunes."
    new "Gideon looked out towards the end of the road and out across the dunes."

    old "I don't think you're wrong about that...but he's still the boss."
    new "I don't think you're wrong about that...but he's still the boss."

    old "But we're his advisors. Isn't it our job to keep him from making a mistake like this?"
    new "But we're his advisors. Isn't it our job to keep him from making a mistake like this?"

    old "Gideon nodded."
    new "Gideon nodded."

    old "Sure, but only if he's actually willing to listen to reason."
    new "Sure, but only if he's actually willing to listen to reason."

    old "If he's going to order the army to march into the desert regardless...best we can do is limit the pain."
    new "If he's going to order the army to march into the desert regardless...best we can do is limit the pain."

    old "Sarah pulled her hand past her scalp, pulling on her own hair as she wiped away the sweat and grime from the desert."
    new "Sarah pulled her hand past her scalp, pulling on her own hair as she wiped away the sweat and grime from the desert."

    old "Limit the pain..."
    new "Limit the pain..."

    old "We march our men into that desert, there is no telling how many will die."
    new "We march our men into that desert, there is no telling how many will die."

    old "We'll make no progress at all, on foot we can't bring most of our supplies, and that's even assuming our destination has supplies to support us."
    new "We'll make no progress at all, on foot we can't bring most of our supplies, and that's even assuming our destination has supplies to support us."

    old "If we cross that desert and there is nothing on the other side..."
    new "If we cross that desert and there is nothing on the other side..."

    old "We're fucked, yeah, that much is true."
    new "We're fucked, yeah, that much is true."

    old "Sarah liked Gideon."
    new "Sarah liked Gideon."

    old "In age, he was closest to her out of all the commanders, but there was also just an easy mutual respect between the two of them."
    new "In age, he was closest to her out of all the commanders, but there was also just an easy mutual respect between the two of them."

    old "It shouldn't have been remarkable, but in a mercenary company, women were generally perceived with suspicion."
    new "It shouldn't have been remarkable, but in a mercenary company, women were generally perceived with suspicion."

    old "Gideon was rare in that he actually seemed to consider her the equal that she was."
    new "Gideon was rare in that he actually seemed to consider her the equal that she was."

    old "He was agreeable enough that they often saw the world the same way, but he wasn't so spineless that he'd simply blindly agree to whatever she said."
    new "He was agreeable enough that they often saw the world the same way, but he wasn't so spineless that he'd simply blindly agree to whatever she said."

    old "Whenever she'd find herself making a mistake, she knew he would call her on it."
    new "Whenever she'd find herself making a mistake, she knew he would call her on it."

    old "She liked that about him too."
    new "She liked that about him too."

    old "So, any ideas, cause the only one I see is suicide, and I'm not about to suggest that."
    new "So, any ideas, cause the only one I see is suicide, and I'm not about to suggest that."

    old "True, but we can't go and tell him to fuck off either."
    new "True, but we can't go and tell him to fuck off either."

    old "Gideon stroked his chin."
    new "Gideon stroked his chin."

    old "So what if we convince him to call it off himself?"
    new "So what if we convince him to call it off himself?"

    old "Sarah observed him."
    new "Sarah observed him."

    old "Well, what if we go back to him with a plan, a real enough plan that makes it sound like we actually thought it over, but simultaneously a bad plan."
    new "Well, what if we go back to him with a plan, a real enough plan that makes it sound like we actually thought it over, but simultaneously a bad plan."

    old "Sarah nodded, understanding where he was going."
    new "Sarah nodded, understanding where he was going."

    old "We give him an option, but it's so fucked he'll draw his own conclusions."
    new "We give him an option, but it's so fucked he'll draw his own conclusions."

    old "He's happy we actually did our jobs, we're happy we won't be marching to death in a desert."
    new "He's happy we actually did our jobs, we're happy we won't be marching to death in a desert."

    old "Sarah saw the wisdom in it."
    new "Sarah saw the wisdom in it."

    old "It wasn't ideal, but it was as close of a chance they had of averting disaster."
    new "It wasn't ideal, but it was as close of a chance they had of averting disaster."

    old "Together, at the edge of the world, under the merciless desert sun, the two plotted as best they could."
    new "Together, at the edge of the world, under the merciless desert sun, the two plotted as best they could."

    old "Half an hour passed before they concluded their discussion and went to confront Vaelen."
    new "Half an hour passed before they concluded their discussion and went to confront Vaelen."

    old "Arriving in Vaelen's tent, they found him already waiting for them."
    new "Arriving in Vaelen's tent, they found him already waiting for them."

    old "Have you found me the answer I'm looking for?"
    new "Have you found me the answer I'm looking for?"

    old "Sarah nodded, stepping forward."
    new "Sarah nodded, stepping forward."

    old "Yes, we have."
    new "Yes, we have."

    old "Vaelen gestured at her."
    new "Vaelen gestured at her."

    old "Well, out with it then."
    new "Well, out with it then."

    old "Sarah gathered her words carefully, then spoke."
    new "Sarah gathered her words carefully, then spoke."

    old "With the condition of the road going forward, our wagons will simply be inoperable."
    new "With the condition of the road going forward, our wagons will simply be inoperable."

    old "The alternative would be to proceed on foot, but this would mean leaving behind the majority of our supplies."
    new "The alternative would be to proceed on foot, but this would mean leaving behind the majority of our supplies."

    old "The only viable option would be to break the wheels on some of the wagons and re-build them with a sort of sled-like construction."
    new "The only viable option would be to break the wheels on some of the wagons and re-build them with a sort of sled-like construction."

    old "This will allow them to be pulled across the sand."
    new "This will allow them to be pulled across the sand."

    old "However, our horses are barely suited for the road as it is, and they won't serve us much further into the desert."
    new "However, our horses are barely suited for the road as it is, and they won't serve us much further into the desert."

    old "This means that soldiers will have to pull the converted wagons, and we don't have enough soldiers to bring all the wagons."
    new "This means that soldiers will have to pull the converted wagons, and we don't have enough soldiers to bring all the wagons."

    old "And so that will mean still having to abandon close to eighty-percent of our current wagons."
    new "And so that will mean still having to abandon close to eighty-percent of our current wagons."

    old "We will have to prioritize wagons containing water and food, so in essence...we would have to abandon nearly all war loot from Bagrad."
    new "We will have to prioritize wagons containing water and food, so in essence...we would have to abandon nearly all war loot from Bagrad."

    old "Sarah decided to stop speaking, letting her words linger."
    new "Sarah decided to stop speaking, letting her words linger."

    old "It was an unacceptable solution."
    new "It was an unacceptable solution."

    old "The burden that a march on foot through the desert imposed, combined with asking the soldiers to abandon their stolen goods, it would be too much to ask of them."
    new "The burden that a march on foot through the desert imposed, combined with asking the soldiers to abandon their stolen goods, it would be too much to ask of them."

    old "I'll draft the orders right away. We need to be moving before nightfall, I want us to make up for lost time."
    new "I'll draft the orders right away. We need to be moving before nightfall, I want us to make up for lost time."

    old "Sarah felt his words hit her like a punch to her stomach."
    new "Sarah felt his words hit her like a punch to her stomach."

    old "She turned to Gideon, trying to speak to him with her eyes."
    new "She turned to Gideon, trying to speak to him with her eyes."

    old "He seemed as lost as she was."
    new "He seemed as lost as she was."

    old "She motioned for him to speak up."
    new "She motioned for him to speak up."

    old "Sir, you understand that-"
    new "Sir, you understand that-"

    old "I do. I understand the demands I am making, and that they will not be easy."
    new "I do. I understand the demands I am making, and that they will not be easy."

    old "Sir, this goes beyond that."
    new "Sir, this goes beyond that."

    old "If we ask the men to abandon their loot..."
    new "If we ask the men to abandon their loot..."

    old "Vaelen waved his hand, dismissing the concern."
    new "Vaelen waved his hand, dismissing the concern."

    old "I will sign the order, in my name. There won't be a soldier in the camp that will disobey such a direct order."
    new "I will sign the order, in my name. There won't be a soldier in the camp that will disobey such a direct order."

    old "Vaelen's pen flashes across a series of documents, applying his signature."
    new "Vaelen's pen flashes across a series of documents, applying his signature."

    old "He grabbed the documents and handed them out to them."
    new "He grabbed the documents and handed them out to them."

    old "Go, make the preparations."
    new "Go, make the preparations."

    old "Get this convoy moving. You find anyone objecting, feel free to have them whipped."
    new "Get this convoy moving. You find anyone objecting, feel free to have them whipped."

    old "With that, the matter was settled."
    new "With that, the matter was settled."

    old "Sarah arrived at Gideon's tent only a moment later."
    new "Sarah arrived at Gideon's tent only a moment later."

    old "This is insane. We can't go through with this."
    new "This is insane. We can't go through with this."

    old "I agree, but we don't have a choice. He's going to go through with this no matter what."
    new "I agree, but we don't have a choice. He's going to go through with this no matter what."

    old "So what then? We just march our men into certain death?"
    new "So what then? We just march our men into certain death?"

    old "Sarah watched as Gideon sat down, rubbing his temples."
    new "Sarah watched as Gideon sat down, rubbing his temples."

    old "We've done all we can in terms of talking sense into him. If he won't listen, I don't know what else there is left to do."
    new "We've done all we can in terms of talking sense into him. If he won't listen, I don't know what else there is left to do."

    old "Sarah paced back and forth in the tent."
    new "Sarah paced back and forth in the tent."

    old "After a while, she finally stopped and turned to face Gideon again."
    new "After a while, she finally stopped and turned to face Gideon again."

    old "A lot of people are going to die if we do this. Our people, the ones we're supposed to be responsible for."
    new "A lot of people are going to die if we do this. Our people, the ones we're supposed to be responsible for."

    old "I'm not any happier about this than you."
    new "I'm not any happier about this than you."

    old "And still we press on?"
    new "And still we press on?"

    old "We...we'll just have to trust that he has a plan. Who knows, maybe it will all work out like it always does."
    new "We...we'll just have to trust that he has a plan. Who knows, maybe it will all work out like it always does."

    old "Gideon's voice trailed off as though he had failed to convince even himself."
    new "Gideon's voice trailed off as though he had failed to convince even himself."

    old "For a moment longer, the two stood in silence, searching for a solution that didn't exist."
    new "For a moment longer, the two stood in silence, searching for a solution that didn't exist."

    old "In the end, they did the only thing they could, and followed Vaelen's orders."
    new "In the end, they did the only thing they could, and followed Vaelen's orders."

    old "Passed down from commanders, to officers, down to the rank-and-file of the mercenary company, the word slowly spread."
    new "Passed down from commanders, to officers, down to the rank-and-file of the mercenary company, the word slowly spread."

    old "All reacted with the same incredulity."
    new "All reacted with the same incredulity."

    old "But as the orders were repeated, disbelief gave way to growing rage."
    new "But as the orders were repeated, disbelief gave way to growing rage."

    old "Shouting, screaming and even occasional bouts of violence."
    new "Shouting, screaming and even occasional bouts of violence."

    old "Each man had become rich off their campaign in Bagrad, and each was now asked to leave their wealth behind in the sands of the desert."
    new "Each man had become rich off their campaign in Bagrad, and each was now asked to leave their wealth behind in the sands of the desert."

    old "They'd return, they were promised, but few believed so."
    new "They'd return, they were promised, but few believed so."

    old "In their minds, each had spent their fortune a hundred times over, and now instead, they were given only the promise of a hollow march."
    new "In their minds, each had spent their fortune a hundred times over, and now instead, they were given only the promise of a hollow march."

    old "A violent, brutal campaign deeper into a forsaken desert."
    new "A violent, brutal campaign deeper into a forsaken desert."

    old "On the other side, no promises of plunder or glory, only the name of a town that meant nothing to any of them."
    new "On the other side, no promises of plunder or glory, only the name of a town that meant nothing to any of them."

    old "The most resistant of them were punished, and before long, the men committed themselves to carrying out the work that seemed so bizarre to them."
    new "The most resistant of them were punished, and before long, the men committed themselves to carrying out the work that seemed so bizarre to them."

    old "There was of course the alternative, to turn around and walk back the five days to Bagrad, but that was a death sentence."
    new "There was of course the alternative, to turn around and walk back the five days to Bagrad, but that was a death sentence."

    old "Behind them, certain death, ahead of them, a likelihood of death."
    new "Behind them, certain death, ahead of them, a likelihood of death."

    old "Each knew they could not truly resist, and so each yielded."
    new "Each knew they could not truly resist, and so each yielded."

    old "But Sarah could see in their eyes what most of the other officers and commanders failed to see."
    new "But Sarah could see in their eyes what most of the other officers and commanders failed to see."

    old "She could see that these men and their submission, did not equal their consent."
    new "She could see that these men and their submission, did not equal their consent."

    old "She could see how each of these men who now did as they were told, added their outrage and hatred to the ledger of their soul."
    new "She could see how each of these men who now did as they were told, added their outrage and hatred to the ledger of their soul."

    old "Growing and accumulating within them, the weight of their anger."
    new "Growing and accumulating within them, the weight of their anger."

    old "They did as they were told, but a cold rage was growing in them."
    new "They did as they were told, but a cold rage was growing in them."

    old "Did Vaelen not see it, she wondered, or did he not want to see it? Did he not care?"
    new "Did Vaelen not see it, she wondered, or did he not want to see it? Did he not care?"

    old "Sarah wished she knew the answer to any of it. Instead, she merely excercised control over what little she could affect, and instructed the men on rebuilding the wagons."
    new "Sarah wished she knew the answer to any of it. Instead, she merely excercised control over what little she could affect, and instructed the men on rebuilding the wagons."

    old "The wooden wheels splintered as hammers struck them."
    new "The wooden wheels splintered as hammers struck them."

    old "The slabs of wood were mounted underneath those carts deemed most essential, the food supplies, the water storage."
    new "The slabs of wood were mounted underneath those carts deemed most essential, the food supplies, the water storage."

    old "The rest of the wagons were left behind by the side of the road, a fortune left to nothing but the elements."
    new "The rest of the wagons were left behind by the side of the road, a fortune left to nothing but the elements."

    old "To the men, Sarah could see that this wealth meant much more than just the monetary value."
    new "To the men, Sarah could see that this wealth meant much more than just the monetary value."

    old "It was the thing they had risked their lives for."
    new "It was the thing they had risked their lives for."

    old "This was how all mercenaries lived. They risked their life for wealth, and then they were afforded the chance to spent it."
    new "This was how all mercenaries lived. They risked their life for wealth, and then they were afforded the chance to spent it."

    old "Spending the wealth would remind them later of why they fought, motivate them to suffer the hardships of martial life."
    new "Spending the wealth would remind them later of why they fought, motivate them to suffer the hardships of martial life."

    old "That promise, of war, then comfort, had now been crudely violated by Vaelen."
    new "That promise, of war, then comfort, had now been crudely violated by Vaelen."

    old "Trial now followed war, and no promise of comfort seemed near."
    new "Trial now followed war, and no promise of comfort seemed near."

    old "And still they labored."
    new "And still they labored."

    old "Shattering the wheels of the wagons and transforming their convoy to one that could withstand the brutal road ahead."
    new "Shattering the wheels of the wagons and transforming their convoy to one that could withstand the brutal road ahead."

    old "With great worry, Sarah overlooked them."
    new "With great worry, Sarah overlooked them."

